⏺ That gives you three distinct pillars, and the framing needs to
   hold all three. A non-X version that still encompasses them:

  ▎ "Modernize the Foo Bar release process so that validated
  ▎ artifacts ship without rebuilding, downstream components are
  ▎ tested before release, and releasability is continuously
  ▎ scored — eliminating manual gates and gaining 50% efficiency."

  The three pillars mapped:
  - "validated artifacts ship without rebuilding" — promotable builds
  - "downstream components tested before release" — cross-product validation
  - "releasability continuously scored" — the dashboard, health indicators

  What you give up vs. the original: "shared standard" and "autorollout."
  What you keep: the actual work the team cares about day-to-day.
